  "doc_id": "37635",
  "text": "These losses are also correlated with a loss of skeletal muscle strength [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Sarcopenia, characterised by progressive and generalised loss of skeletal muscle mass (SMM) and strength associated with ageing, contributes to functional and physical disability, including poor quality of life [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The assessment of body composition, in particular SMM, is therefore an important component of assessing health status in an ageing population.",
